    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Made this with a big ol&#39; pot of cannellini beans this weekend. I used Broccoli Rabe instead of endive (still the bitter green contrast to the sweet and smooth beans)that looked to be just picked; crunchy and bright green with barely anything to be trimmed off.  I also added (NOT that it really needed it) some bits of sauteed, crunchy Italian sausage and served it all over -ok, ok this was going way overboard- polenta with a ton of Parmesan Reggiano in it. It was the perfect rainy day dinner after a lovely walk in our Pacific NW grey day.<br />Thank you for a perfectly wonderful blog, Molly.  I look forward to, and am very excited by, any new posts.</p>
    </div>

