    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I made these with &quot;haricots lingots&quot; (I bought them at the market in the French town where I&#39;m living.) I cheated a little bit on the recipe&#8211;I worried I hadn&#39;t washed my beans enough before soaking, because my soaking water looked a little dirty. So, I used a coeur bouillon cube that I had that was lemon and herb flavored to make the base bean recipe. I used those beans to make this tonight and oh my god&#8230;these beans were LIFE CHANGING. Seriously. They were so so good. it was incredible. Hurray!!!! And because dried beans are soooo cheap and soooooo compact I have enough left to make them again! Thank you!</p>
